#Group Management :

What is a group in Linux, and why is it used?
In Linux, there can be multiple users (those who use/operate the system), 
and groups are nothing but a collection of users. Groups make it easy to manage users with the 
same security and access privileges. A user can be part of different groups. The ‘groups’ command is 
a powerful tool that allows administrators to view the group memberships of a user and retrieve information about user groups on a Linux 
System.

How do you create a new group in Linux?
To create a new group, use the groupadd command

How do you delete a group in Linux?
The groupdel command is used to delete an existing group from the system ex. groupdel option groupname 

What is the purpose of the /etc/group file?
The /etc/group file stores group information and is the default configuration file.

