#Process management :

How do you view running processes in Linux?
The ps command is one of the most commonly used commands to display information about running processes.

What is the difference between foreground and background processes?
ANS:- A process that connects to the terminal is called a foreground job. 
A job is said to be in the foreground because it can communicate with the user via the screen and the keyboard.
On the other hand, a process that disconnects from the terminal and cannot communicate with the user is called a background job


